President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. The nominees include Courtney Simmons Elwood for General Counsel of the Central Intelligence Agency, Noel J. Francisco for Solicitor General of the Department of Justice, Ajit V. Pai for Member of the Federal Communications Commission, Jeffrey A. Rosen for Deputy Secretary for the Department of Transportation, and John J. Sullivan for General Counsel for the Department of Defense. Additionally, Trump announced his intent to appoint Tony E. Sayegh, Jr. as Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of the Treasury. These individuals have extensive experience in their respective fields and will contribute to Trump's goal of making America great again.